The #rstats documentation states - "an object can be atomic but not a vector". Example -

x <- c(1, 2)
attr(x, "temp") <- "A"
is.vector(x)
is.atomic(x)

but the reverse is also true (x below is a vector but not atomic) -

x <- list(1, 2)
is.atomic(x)
is.vector(x)
